{"id":"KBs27GkhAPvIKzgy","meta":{"instanceId":"46a9123f150f9dbd2af50a385a319aa488ee2fb14ce95ea74093777b69e2f4a2","templateCredsSetupCompleted":true},"name":"Customer Escalation Detector","tags":[],"nodes":[{"id":"bf09712f-5e35-432d-912a-f3cdd2e35c36","name":"Sticky Note","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[2160,912],"parameters":{"color":2,"width":704,"height":1040,"content":"# Customer Escalation Detector\n\nDetects refund requests, cancellation intent, legal threats, angry customers, chargeback threats, and executive escalation demands across Gmail, Zendesk, Intercom, and HelpScout. Routes critical and high-severity cases to Slack and Linear. Silently discards clean messages.\n\n\n---\n\n## How it works\n\n1. A message arrives via webhook from any connected support source.\n2. **Normalize Inbound Message** maps the source-specific payload into a unified shape customer name, email, subject, body, source URL.\n3. **Claude** classifies the message: detects up to 8 signal types, assigns severity (critical/high/medium/low/none), extracts trigger phrases verbatim, and writes a suggested opening reply.\n4. **If Escalation** stops the flow silently for clean messages (severity = none).\n5. **Build Actions** constructs the Slack message, Linear ticket, and routing decisions.\n6. **Post to Slack** always fires for any escalation.\n7. **Create Linear Ticket** fires for critical, high, and medium severity.\n8. **Notify Manager** fires only for critical and high a direct Slack DM to the manager on call.\n\n---\n\n\n## Setup steps\n\n- [ ] Add Anthropic API credentials to Anthropic Chat Model\n- [ ] Set your Slack channel in Post to Slack (e.g. `#escalations`)\n- [ ] Set your manager's Slack user ID in Notify Manager\n- [ ] Set your Linear team ID in Create Linear Ticket\n- [ ] Connect your source(s): configure Zendesk / Intercom / HelpScout to POST to the **Receive Message** webhook URL, OR use the Gmail Trigger path instead of the webhook\n\n---\n\n## Severity SLAs\n\n**Critical**: 15 min (legal threat, chargeback, angry+cancel)\n**High**: 1 hour (cancellation, executive escalation)\n**Medium**: 4 hours (refund request, angry, public threat)\n**Low**: 24 hours (negative sentiment only)\n\n---\n\n## Sources supported\n\nGmail · Zendesk · Intercom · HelpScout · Raw webhook (test/custom)\n\nAll sources normalize to the same internal schema adding a new source means adding one branch to the Normalize node only."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"6a39ccc3-4755-4d5d-8652-762cbd6feb12","name":"Sticky Note1","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[2928,912],"parameters":{"color":7,"width":480,"height":608,"content":"## Ingest and normalize\n\nWebhook receives from any source. Normalize node maps Gmail, Zendesk, Intercom, HelpScout, and raw payloads to one unified shape."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"eb141507-9100-42b0-88ba-dcfabcf74f0c","name":"Sticky Note2","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[3440,912],"parameters":{"color":7,"width":528,"height":608,"content":"## AI classification\n\nClaude detects 8 signal types, assigns severity, extracts verbatim trigger phrases, and writes a suggested response opening. Structured output parser enforces the schema."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"9d0d67ef-d02a-4193-b8b1-5a01375ecfdf","name":"Sticky Note3","type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","position":[4048,912],"parameters":{"color":7,"width":992,"height":704,"content":"## Route and act\n\nSlack alert always fires for escalations. Linear ticket for critical/high/medium. Manager DM only for critical/high. Clean messages (severity=none) are discarded silently."},"typeVersion":1},{"id":"38ce2e10-e864-463d-ae7c-c38efd87cc09","name":"Receive Message","type":"n8n-nodes-base.webhook","position":[3008,1152],"webhookId":"escalation-detector-001","parameters":{"path":"escalation-detector","options":{},"httpMethod":"POST","responseMode":"lastNode"},"typeVersion":2},{"id":"f8363c1e-7f02-43ec-81e9-ab5a2e79ab7d","name":"Acknowledge Receipt","type":"n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook","position":[3008,1360],"parameters":{"options":{"responseCode":200},"respondWith":"json","responseBody":"{\"status\": \"received\", \"message\": \"Message queued for escalation analysis\"}"},"typeVersion":1.1},{"id":"cbb14000-fe0c-434f-8106-8a2faeed67da","name":"Normalize Inbound Message","type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","position":[3248,1152],"parameters":{"jsCode":"// Normalize messages from any source into a unified shape\n// Sources: Gmail, Zendesk, Intercom, HelpScout, or raw webhook\nconst body = $input.first().json;\n\nlet normalized = {\n  source: 'webhook',\n  customer_name: null,\n  customer_email: null,\n  subject: null,\n  message_body: null,\n  source_url: null,\n  raw: body\n};\n\n// Gmail (via n8n Gmail Trigger)\nif (body.payload?.headers || body.threadId) {\n  const headers = body.payload?.headers || [];\n  const get = (name) => headers.find(h => h.name?.toLowerCase() === name.toLowerCase())?.value || null;\n  const textPart = body.payload?.parts?.find(p => p.mimeType === 'text/plain');\n  const decoded = textPart?.body?.data\n    ? Buffer.from(textPart.body.data, 'base64').toString('utf-8')\n    : body.snippet || '';\n  normalized = {\n    source: 'gmail',\n    customer_name: get('from')?.replace(/<.*>/, '').trim() || null,\n    customer_email: get('from')?.match(/<(.+)>/)?.[1] || get('from') || null,\n    subject: get('subject'),\n    message_body: decoded,\n    source_url: `https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox/${body.threadId}`,\n    raw: body\n  };\n}\n// Zendesk (webhook payload)\nelse if (body.ticket?.id || body.ticket_id) {\n  const ticket = body.ticket || body;\n  normalized = {\n    source: 'zendesk',\n    customer_name: ticket.requester?.name || body.requester_name || null,\n    customer_email: ticket.requester?.email || body.requester_email || null,\n    subject: ticket.subject || body.subject || null,\n    message_body: ticket.description || ticket.latest_comment?.body || body.description || null,\n    source_url: ticket.url || null,\n    raw: body\n  };\n}\n// Intercom (webhook payload)\nelse if (body.data?.item?.type === 'conversation' || body.type === 'notification_event') {\n  const convo = body.data?.item || body;\n  const firstMsg = convo.conversation_message || convo.source;\n  const contact = convo.contacts?.contacts?.[0] || convo.user || {};\n  normalized = {\n    source: 'intercom',\n    customer_name: contact.name || null,\n    customer_email: contact.email || null,\n    subject: firstMsg?.subject || null,\n    message_body: firstMsg?.body?.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '') || null,\n    source_url: convo.links?.conversation_web || null,\n    raw: body\n  };\n}\n// HelpScout (webhook payload)\nelse if (body.item?.type === 'conversation' && body.item?.mailboxId) {\n  const item = body.item;\n  const customer = item.primaryCustomer || {};\n  normalized = {\n    source: 'helpscout',\n    customer_name: `${customer.firstName || ''} ${customer.lastName || ''}`.trim() || null,\n    customer_email: customer.email || null,\n    subject: item.subject || null,\n    message_body: item.preview || item.threads?.[0]?.body?.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '') || null,\n    source_url: item._links?.web?.href || null,\n    raw: body\n  };\n}\n// Raw / test payload\nelse if (body.message_body) {\n  normalized = {\n    source: body.source || 'webhook',\n    customer_name: body.customer_name || null,\n    customer_email: body.customer_email || null,\n    subject: body.subject || null,\n    message_body: body.message_body,\n    source_url: body.source_url || null,\n    raw: body\n  };\n}\n\nif (!normalized.message_body) {\n  throw new Error(`Could not extract message body from ${normalized.source} payload. Check the webhook payload format.`);\n}\n\nreturn [{ json: normalized }];"},"typeVersion":2},{"id":"4c2f51b9-603c-4221-8105-a1d914468170","name":"Classify Escalation","type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent","position":[3520,1152],"parameters":{"text":"=Analyze this customer message for escalation signals.\n\nSource: {{ $json.source }}\nCustomer: {{ $json.customer_name || 'Unknown' }} ({{ $json.customer_email || 'no email' }})\nSubject: {{ $json.subject || '(no subject)' }}\nMessage:\n{{ $json.message_body }}\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON following your schema exactly.","options":{"systemMessage":"You are a senior customer support analyst. Your job is to analyze inbound customer messages and detect escalation signals with high precision.\n\n## Escalation categories (detect ALL that apply)\n- refund_request: customer explicitly asks for money back, refund, chargeback, or compensation\n- cancellation_intent: customer wants to cancel, downgrade, not renew, or threatens to leave\n- legal_threat: mentions lawyer, lawsuit, attorney, BBB, FTC, court, legal action, regulatory complaint\n- executive_escalation: asks to speak to CEO, founder, VP, director, or \"someone senior\"\n- angry_sentiment: hostile, aggressive, or highly frustrated tone, swearing, all caps, exclamation abuse\n- negative_sentiment: clearly unhappy but not hostile, disappointed, let down, frustrated\n- chargeback_threat: mentions credit card dispute, PayPal dispute, bank reversal\n- public_threat: threatens to post on social media, write a review, tell others\n\n## Severity levels\n- critical: legal_threat OR chargeback_threat OR (angry_sentiment AND cancellation_intent) — respond within 15 minutes\n- high: cancellation_intent OR executive_escalation OR (angry_sentiment AND refund_request) — respond within 1 hour\n- medium: refund_request OR angry_sentiment OR public_threat — respond within 4 hours\n- low: negative_sentiment only — respond within 24 hours\n\n## Rules\n- Be precise. Do not over-classify neutral complaints as escalations.\n- A customer asking \"how do I cancel?\" is NOT cancellation_intent, it's a support question.\n- A customer saying \"I want to cancel my subscription\" IS cancellation_intent.\n- Extract verbatim phrases that triggered each flag.\n- Suggested response should be professional, empathetic, and tailored to the specific signals detected."},"promptType":"define","hasOutputParser":true},"typeVersion":3},{"id":"fe52eafc-fe53-4928-8e2f-62f8e5ed6b7b","name":"Anthropic Chat Model","type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatAnthropic","position":[3472,1392],"parameters":{"model":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","cachedResultName":"Claude Sonnet 4.5"},"options":{"temperature":0.1}},"credentials":{"anthropicApi":{"id":"5GacE7Rg8qo0c4md","name":"Anthropic connection"}},"typeVersion":1.3},{"id":"c4d743e7-2abb-4f15-899b-a3899100b12e","name":"Structured Output Parser","type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.outputParserStructured","position":[3696,1376],"parameters":{"autoFix":true,"schemaType":"manual","inputSchema":"{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"escalation_detected\": {\n      \"type\": \"boolean\"\n    },\n    \"severity\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\n        \"critical\",\n        \"high\",\n        \"medium\",\n        \"low\",\n        \"none\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"signals\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"enum\": [\n          \"refund_request\",\n          \"cancellation_intent\",\n          \"legal_threat\",\n          \"executive_escalation\",\n          \"angry_sentiment\",\n          \"negative_sentiment\",\n          \"chargeback_threat\",\n          \"public_threat\"\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    \"trigger_phrases\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"string\"\n      },\n      \"description\": \"Verbatim phrases from the message that triggered the flags\"\n    },\n    \"sentiment_score\": {\n      \"type\": \"number\",\n      \"description\": \"-1.0 (very negative) to 1.0 (very positive)\"\n    },\n    \"summary\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"One sentence: what the customer wants and why they are upset\"\n    },\n    \"suggested_response_tone\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"enum\": [\n        \"urgent_empathetic\",\n        \"empathetic_firm\",\n        \"empathetic\",\n        \"informational\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"suggested_response_opening\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"First 1-2 sentences of a suggested reply to this customer\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\n    \"escalation_detected\",\n    \"severity\",\n    \"signals\",\n    \"trigger_phrases\",\n    \"sentiment_score\",\n    \"summary\",\n    \"suggested_response_tone\",\n    \"suggested_response_opening\"\n  ],\n  \"additionalProperties\": false\n}"},"typeVersion":1.2},{"id":"36e4f5ab-8648-4908-8b4b-82863b1f32de","name":"Build Actions","type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","position":[3840,1152],"parameters":{"jsCode":"// Build Slack message, Linear ticket data, and routing decision\nconst ai = $input.first().json.output || $input.first().json;\nconst msg = $('Normalize Inbound Message').first().json;\n\nif (!ai.escalation_detected || ai.severity === 'none') {\n  return [{ json: { skip: true } }];\n}\n\nconst severityConfig = {\n  critical: { color: '#FF0000', sla: '15 minutes', linearPriority: 1 },\n  high:     { color: '#FF6600', sla: '1 hour',     linearPriority: 2 },\n  medium:   { color: '#FFB800', sla: '4 hours',    linearPriority: 3 },\n  low:      { color: '#00B300', sla: '24 hours',   linearPriority: 4 }\n};\n\nconst cfg = severityConfig[ai.severity] || severityConfig.medium;\n\nconst signalLabels = {\n  refund_request: 'Refund request',\n  cancellation_intent: 'Cancellation intent',\n  legal_threat: 'Legal threat',\n  executive_escalation: 'Executive escalation',\n  angry_sentiment: 'Angry sentiment',\n  negative_sentiment: 'Negative sentiment',\n  chargeback_threat: 'Chargeback threat',\n  public_threat: 'Public threat'\n};\n\nconst sourceLabel = {\n  gmail: 'Gmail',\n  zendesk: 'Zendesk',\n  intercom: 'Intercom',\n  helpscout: 'HelpScout',\n  webhook: 'Webhook'\n};\n\n// Slack message\nconst slackLines = [\n  `*Customer Escalation Detected — ${ai.severity.toUpperCase()}*`,\n  '',\n  `*Source:* ${sourceLabel[msg.source] || msg.source}  ·  *SLA:* ${cfg.sla}`,\n  `*Customer:* ${msg.customer_name || 'Unknown'}  ·  ${msg.customer_email || ''}`,\n  msg.subject ? `*Subject:* ${msg.subject}` : '',\n  '',\n  `*Summary:* ${ai.summary}`,\n  '',\n  `*Signals detected:*`,\n  ...(ai.signals || []).map(s => `  • ${signalLabels[s] || s}`),\n  '',\n];\n\nif (ai.trigger_phrases?.length) {\n  slackLines.push(`*Key phrases:*`);\n  ai.trigger_phrases.slice(0, 3).forEach(p => slackLines.push(`  _\"${p}\"_`));\n  slackLines.push('');\n}\n\nslackLines.push(`*Suggested opening:*`);\nslackLines.push(`_${ai.suggested_response_opening}_`);\n\nif (msg.source_url) {\n  slackLines.push('');\n  slackLines.push(`<${msg.source_url}|View original message>`);\n}\n\n// Linear ticket description\nconst linearDescription = [\n  `## Escalation — ${ai.severity.toUpperCase()}`,\n  '',\n  `**Source:** ${sourceLabel[msg.source] || msg.source}`,\n  `**Customer:** ${msg.customer_name || 'Unknown'} (${msg.customer_email || 'no email'})`,\n  `**SLA:** Respond within ${cfg.sla}`,\n  `**Sentiment score:** ${ai.sentiment_score?.toFixed(2)}`,\n  '',\n  `## Summary`,\n  ai.summary,\n  '',\n  `## Signals detected`,\n  ...(ai.signals || []).map(s => `- ${signalLabels[s] || s}`),\n  '',\n  `## Trigger phrases`,\n  ...(ai.trigger_phrases || []).map(p => `- \"${p}\"`),\n  '',\n  `## Suggested response opening`,\n  ai.suggested_response_opening,\n  '',\n  `## Original message`,\n  '```',\n  (msg.message_body || '').slice(0, 2000),\n  '```'\n].join('\\n');\n\nconst linearTitle = `[${ai.severity.toUpperCase()}] ${msg.customer_name || 'Customer'} — ${(ai.signals || []).map(s => s.replace(/_/g,' ')).join(', ')}`;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    skip: false,\n    slackMessage: slackLines.filter(l => l !== '').join('\\n'),\n    linearTitle: linearTitle.slice(0, 100),\n    linearDescription,\n    linearPriority: cfg.linearPriority,\n    severity: ai.severity,\n    signals: ai.signals,\n    customer_email: msg.customer_email,\n    customer_name: msg.customer_name,\n    source: msg.source,\n    createLinearTicket: ['critical','high','medium'].includes(ai.severity),\n    notifyManager: ['critical','high'].includes(ai.severity)\n  }\n}];"},"typeVersion":2},{"id":"715eb2c8-a381-444f-8412-593f66186fa5","name":"If Escalation","type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","position":[4096,1152],"parameters":{"options":{},"conditions":{"options":{"version":3,"leftValue":"","caseSensitive":true,"typeValidation":"strict"},"combinator":"and","conditions":[{"id":"skip-check","operator":{"type":"boolean","operation":"equals"},"leftValue":"={{ $json.skip }}","rightValue":false}]}},"typeVersion":2.3},{"id":"4ab4bb2a-72b6-41f8-95c4-67d703dfb1c0","name":"Post to Slack","type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","position":[4480,1136],"webhookId":"55ef5861-308c-441f-acf9-4f1ee4b042d0","parameters":{"text":"={{ $json.slackMessage }}","select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#escalations"},"otherOptions":{"unfurl_links":false,"includeLinkToWorkflow":false},"authentication":"oAuth2"},"credentials":{"slackOAuth2Api":{"id":"ZhdPhKRrjqSZXid7","name":"Slack connection"}},"typeVersion":2.4},{"id":"c851b36f-9af5-4cf7-a877-d17881e82a77","name":"If Create Ticket","type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","position":[4480,1296],"parameters":{"options":{},"conditions":{"options":{"version":3,"leftValue":"","caseSensitive":true,"typeValidation":"strict"},"combinator":"and","conditions":[{"id":"linear-check","operator":{"type":"boolean","operation":"equals"},"leftValue":"={{ $json.createLinearTicket }}","rightValue":true}]}},"typeVersion":2.3},{"id":"43228979-9aed-4ec6-9d9a-4fa1ac0f02bf","name":"Create Linear Ticket","type":"n8n-nodes-base.linear","position":[4800,1280],"parameters":{"title":"={{ $json.linearTitle }}","teamId":"REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_LINEAR_TEAM_ID","authentication":"oAuth2","additionalFields":{"description":"={{ $json.linearDescription }}"}},"typeVersion":1.1},{"id":"a6da67de-2438-4064-a97e-5d8d585f3b61","name":"If Notify Manager","type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","position":[4480,1456],"parameters":{"options":{},"conditions":{"options":{"version":3,"leftValue":"","caseSensitive":true,"typeValidation":"strict"},"combinator":"and","conditions":[{"id":"manager-check","operator":{"type":"boolean","operation":"equals"},"leftValue":"={{ $json.notifyManager }}","rightValue":true}]}},"typeVersion":2.3},{"id":"422b6706-8656-413e-9a17-0ffa9567ebaf","name":"Notify Manager","type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","position":[4800,1440],"webhookId":"ba907f6f-09a5-4298-8663-64c11a56c3d6","parameters":{"text":"=🚨 *Urgent escalation needs your attention — {{ $json.severity.toUpperCase() }}*\n\n*Customer:* {{ $json.customer_name || 'Unknown' }} ({{ $json.customer_email || '' }})\n*Signals:* {{ ($json.signals || []).join(', ') }}\n\nA ticket has been created in Linear. Please review within the SLA window.","user":{"__rl":true,"mode":"id","value":"REPLACE_WITH_MANAGER_SLACK_USER_ID"},"select":"user","otherOptions":{"includeLinkToWorkflow":false},"authentication":"oAuth2"},"credentials":{"slackOAuth2Api":{"id":"ZhdPhKRrjqSZXid7","name":"Slack connection"}},"typeVersion":2.4}],"active":false,"pinData":{},"settings":{"binaryMode":"separate","executionOrder":"v1"},"versionId":"226f45c0-b87b-4244-922c-3d6669e3005d","connections":{"Build Actions":{"main":[[{"node":"If Escalation","type":"main","index":0}]]},"If Escalation":{"main":[[{"node":"Post to Slack","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"If Create Ticket","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"If Notify Manager","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Receive Message":{"main":[[{"node":"Normalize Inbound Message","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Acknowledge Receipt","type":"main","index":0}]]},"If Create Ticket":{"main":[[{"node":"Create Linear Ticket","type":"main","index":0}]]},"If Notify Manager":{"main":[[{"node":"Notify Manager","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Classify Escalation":{"main":[[{"node":"Build Actions","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Anthropic Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Classify Escalation","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0},{"node":"Structured Output Parser","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Structured Output Parser":{"ai_outputParser":[[{"node":"Classify Escalation","type":"ai_outputParser","index":0}]]},"Normalize Inbound Message":{"main":[[{"node":"Classify Escalation","type":"main","index":0}]]}}}